<body>
<p t="240" d="6360">Welcome to Beijing! We are 
brothers, we are all sisters. Yes. </p>
<p t="6600" d="5440">After recently reopening from 3 years of covid 
isolation we are heading to the People&#39;s Republic  </p>
<p t="12040" d="6560">of China, a country we hear so much about, but 
one that most of us know so little of. China&#39;s  </p>
<p t="18600" d="5000">often dubbed &#39;one of the most difficult countries 
to travel to and within&#39;. With a difficult Visa  </p>
<p t="23600" d="5080">policy, the lack of western-based apps we&#39;ve all 
become completely accustomed to when traveling,  </p>
<p t="28680" d="4120">and difficulties using VISA and MasterCard. 
But there&#39;s actually a way to enter China  </p>
<p t="32800" d="4360">without a Visa and a just passport. And 
with that in mind, we hopped on a plane  </p>
<p t="37160" d="8200">and flew to Beijing! Thank you, bye bye. Bye.
Welcome to Beijing airport, welcome to China,  </p>
<p t="45360" d="4400">it is our first time here in China. We haven&#39;t 
quite made it yet, we&#39;ve still got passport  </p>
<p t="49760" d="5680">control to go through, and we&#39;re arriving here 
trying to take advantage of the 144-hour Visa  </p>
<p t="55440" d="5920">free rule that there is for both British citizens 
and Russian citizens, and that&#39;s available if  </p>
<p t="61360" d="6040">you&#39;re flying into Beijing and out of Beijing to 
another country again, which we are. So, um, yeah,  </p>
<p t="67400" d="4440">hopefully everything goes alright at passport 
control, and we&#39;re going to be in Beijing. </p>
<p t="71840" d="5320">We&#39;re in China, oh my god, so excited!
We actually only had to fill in a few  </p>
<p t="77160" d="4120">short forms and have a chat with immigration 
and share our onward travel plans and they  </p>
<p t="81280" d="4480">stamped our passports. It all took around a 
couple of hours, and then we were through. </p>
<p t="85760" d="3240">It seemed like we were the last people 
leaving the airport but we finally made  </p>
<p t="89000" d="4760">it and we can say welcome to China.
The Next Step was to get a cab into  </p>
<p t="93760" d="7280">the City. And Uber, Grab, Bolt, Maxim, 
Yandex, or any of the taxi apps we&#39;re  </p>
<p t="101040" d="5040">used to, are completely useless in China.
So we downloaded an app called Didi travel and I&#39;m  </p>
<p t="106080" d="4080">not going to lie it took us an awfully long time 
to figure it out, because everything is obviously  </p>
<p t="110160" d="5280">in Mandarin, which we don&#39;t speak. But we got 
there in the end! Once we sat in the taxi we were  </p>
<p t="115440" d="4960">greeted by probably the World&#39;s friendliest 
cabbie and despite the language barrier and  </p>
<p t="120400" d="8680">some confusion with how to accept the ride on 
the app our journey went relatively smoothly</p>
<p t="129080" d="4480">[Music]</p>
<p t="133560" d="5840">That was an easy taxi ride! Finally, 
we made it I can&#39;t believe it. </p>
<p t="139400" d="6440">So we landed at 14:30 and the time now is 
18:00, um, you know it took us maybe an  </p>
<p t="145840" d="4240">hour or so to sort out all the documents of 
immigration, and then just all the rest of  </p>
<p t="150080" d="5520">the time trying to sort out the taxi into the 
city. We could have got a train but then we  </p>
<p t="155600" d="5000">would have still had to get a taxi from the main 
train station to here, so we just thought taxi  </p>
<p t="160600" d="15400">all the way. And here we are 3 and a half hours 
later, but we&#39;ve arrived that&#39;s the main thing!</p>
<p t="176000" d="5360">Good morning, last night we were pretty zonked 
to be honest, after getting in. It was a long,  </p>
<p t="181360" d="4160">long travel day, it wasn&#39;t supposed to be. It 
was supposed to be a 3-hour flight, and then a  </p>
<p t="185520" d="4760">quick nip into Beijing centre, but everything&#39;s 
a little bit more complicated when you arrive  </p>
<p t="190280" d="5280">here in China, the usual apps that we&#39;re used to 
when we&#39;re traveling most of the world don&#39;t work,  </p>
<p t="195560" d="5520">so you need to download new apps, sign up to them, 
most of them are only in Chinese which makes it  </p>
<p t="201080" d="4680">a little bit more difficult. You also have to 
sign up to Alipay in order to pay for anything  </p>
<p t="205760" d="4880">with your foreign card. But once we sorted all 
that out, we got into to the city and yeah,  </p>
<p t="210640" d="4920">we&#39;re were a little bit tired. So we went 
out for a little walk, a little look around,  </p>
<p t="215560" d="4360">and um, yeah, we&#39;re up bright and early 
this morning to go and explore Beijing. </p>
<p t="219920" d="4360">I still can&#39;t believe we&#39;re here to be honest, 
it&#39;s absolutely unbelievable, I&#39;m so over the  </p>
<p t="224280" d="3880">moon, so looking forward to seeing a bit of China. 
You know what I&#39;m really looking forward to as  </p>
<p t="228160" d="11480">well starting our day with, you guessed it, 
Peking Chicken, nope, Peking Duck [Laughter]</p>
<p t="239640" d="19520">Looks like a tram. It does look like a 
tram, I thought at first it was a tram.</p>
<p t="259160" d="3160">So if Vietnam was full of motorbikes,  </p>
<p t="262320" d="4920">China is full of normal bikes. Here in Beijing 
when we were driving into the City yesterday,  </p>
<p t="267240" d="4880">everyone was either on little electric 
scooters or bikes, and um, it provides a  </p>
<p t="272120" d="27880">totally different vibe to be honest. It&#39;s a lot 
quieter a lot calmer than than Hanoi yesterday</p>
<p t="300000" d="4520">Everything is just so 
interesting and fascinating here. </p>
<p t="304520" d="20640">We are in China Town. In 
the Real China Town! [Music]</p>
<p t="325160" d="280">fifth</p>
<p t="325440" d="4040">floor</p>
<p t="344240" d="14920">thank you</p>
<p t="363720" d="4680">So, if we read right, this is supposed to be one 
of the oldest restaurant chains here in Beijing,  </p>
<p t="368400" d="4480">and one of the best places to try Peking 
duck. And already when we saw the chefs  </p>
<p t="372880" d="5480">just come past a minute ago with the 
duck, it smelt absolutely incredible,  </p>
<p t="378360" d="7040">and looked even better, I cannot 
wait to try it. I&#39;m so so excited</p>
<p t="385400" d="5080">It&#39;s interesting to feel like everyone knows 
what they&#39;re doing like what they ordering and  </p>
<p t="390480" d="7800">we have not the foggiest clue what&#39;s going 
on. Lost in the corner. Lost in the corner,  </p>
<p t="398280" d="11320">kind of true. The duck looks 
insane it smells so good.</p>
<p t="409600" d="9760">The juice is just dripping down, and 
out to my mouth too. I thought that  </p>
<p t="419360" d="9840">was what you were talking about 
to honest. Sounds so gross.</p>
<p t="429200" d="20143">This pastry is so thin but it holds 
so well. It doesn&#39;t break at all.</p>
<p t="449343" d="6857">It is delicious! [Music]</p>
<p t="456200" d="23120">Guys, we just tried Peking Duck in Peking!</p>
<p t="479320" d="13080">[Music] [Music]</p>
<p t="492400" d="4320">it&#39;s a really really strong flavour of 
green tea. You know when you leave your  </p>
<p t="496720" d="9920">tea bag there for too long in your cup, 
this is what it is, in an ice cream form.</p>
<p t="506640" d="16800">Jasmine green tea, wow, that is so unusual. 
Let&#39;s head to the main Square! Mhm, let&#39;s go!</p>
<p t="523440" d="5400">One first impression of Beijing considering we&#39;re 
in the very centre it&#39;s nowhere near as busy as I  </p>
<p t="528840" d="4440">thought it was going to be. I don&#39;t know why, 
again, it&#39;s just a stereotype you think in  </p>
<p t="533280" d="3920">China you&#39;re going to be cramped up, shoulder 
to- shoulder, there&#39;s just going to be people  </p>
<p t="537200" d="4800">everywhere. But there&#39;s so much space, it seems 
like there&#39;s hardly anyone out on the streets,  </p>
<p t="542000" d="4840">and yeah, you can just you can walk freely, 
between the three of you talk in a line,  </p>
<p t="546840" d="4320">and yeah it&#39;s not crowded at all. We&#39;re in the 
centre of the capital right now. It&#39;s actually  </p>
<p t="551160" d="6360">Sunday today as well, supposed to be the busiest 
day it&#39;s not. You can&#39;t say it&#39;s not busy, it is,  </p>
<p t="557520" d="5720">but not how we expected it. Not crowded, not 
crowded. I didn&#39;t expect the roads to be that  </p>
<p t="563240" d="11960">wide and that big, it feels really spacious. 
[ There were 10,000 bicycle in Beijing. ]</p>
<p t="575200" d="6760">And a couple of Security checks later, welcome 
to Tiananmen Square, a place that I&#39;ve seen a  </p>
<p t="581960" d="5720">thousand times on the news, on different travel 
videos. A place that we&#39;ve dreamed about coming  </p>
<p t="587680" d="6200">for a long, long time. It feels so surreal to 
be here, to be standing on Tiananmen Square,  </p>
<p t="593880" d="3440">looking at the big photo of Chairman 
Mao, looking at all the monuments,  </p>
<p t="597320" d="8600">all the big buildings all around here, 
incredible, absolutely incredible. It&#39;s  </p>
<p t="605920" d="4480">even bigger in real life as well than 
it looks on the TV on the camera. Which,  </p>
<p t="610400" d="4080">to be honest doesn&#39;t usually happen. Usually 
you get to a place and it&#39;s a lot smaller than  </p>
<p t="614480" d="14560">it looks on camera, but yeah, this is massive. 
Wow, incredible, in the very heart of China!</p>
<p t="637240" d="6720">So big! So, I just said, it&#39;s often the case 
that you see something on TV so many times,  </p>
<p t="643960" d="4720">or on different videos, and it looks so much 
bigger than it actually is in real life, but,  </p>
<p t="648680" d="6640">here it&#39;s the opposite. Yeah yeah yeah.
It&#39;s absolutely Grand in scale. </p>
<p t="655320" d="5040">So as foreigners, we need to carry 
our past passports with us everywhere,  </p>
<p t="660360" d="5560">and to get into the square you need to go for 
a few Security checks. They check your bags,  </p>
<p t="665920" d="5600">and they check your passports, and like, everyone 
goes through but I guess locals have this ID cards  </p>
<p t="671520" d="4400">or something like that. But we have to carry 
our passports with us, we learnt that last night  </p>
<p t="675920" d="5080">when we walked into the square in the evening. We 
didn&#39;t have our passports, we were trying to show  </p>
<p t="681000" d="4760">our pictures, uh our pictures. We were trying to 
show pictures of our passports on our phones. And  </p>
<p t="685760" d="16640">it was fine but, he was like &quot;next time just 
make sure you bring a passport&quot;, so we did!</p>
<p t="702400" d="3520">Walking through the middle of Tiananmen 
Square, and seeing all of the internal  </p>
<p t="705920" d="3720">tourists as well. That here are a lot of 
people with suitcases, that are obviously  </p>
<p t="709640" d="6000">passing through Beijing. It&#39;s hard to really 
grasp the size of China, both in terms of area,  </p>
<p t="715640" d="4600">and obviously population. And there&#39;s so many 
different faces that you see from different  </p>
<p t="720240" d="4880">regions of China as well. It&#39;s just incredible and 
yeah, to be right here in the heart of Beijing,  </p>
<p t="725120" d="10240">and to see lots of people that have come here 
from all over the country, it&#39;s, yeah, incredible.</p>
<p t="735360" d="5560">I don&#39;t know as well, despite this being the 
first day of four here in China, I&#39;m already kind  </p>
<p t="740920" d="4640">of sad we&#39;re leaving, and I feel like I really 
want to go off to other regions of the country  </p>
<p t="745560" d="5800">to see how different people live, different 
foods, different cultures. It&#39;s so so varied,  </p>
<p t="751360" d="8800">there&#39;s so many different cultures, and types of 
people, and religions, and histories. And yeah,  </p>
<p t="760160" d="3960">we&#39;re leaving in 4 days, we are going have to 
come back. We need to get Visa and come back.  </p>
<p t="764120" d="14720">We will just get a Visa and come back. Deal. We 
got the little taste of it, we like it, come back.</p>
